FreeBSD and POSIX compliance issues: http://lists.freebsd.org/pipermail/freebsd-standards/2010-April/001936.html

Deleting partitions:

sh -c 'set -x; for i in `cd /dev/; ls *p*`; do echo gpart delete -i ${i##*p} ${i%p*}; done'
sh -c 'set -x; for i in `cd /dev/; ls ad*p*`; do echo gpart delete -i ${i##*p} ${i%p*}; done'
sh -c 'set -x; for i in `cd /dev/; ls da[0-9]* | grep -v s`; do gpart destroy -F $i; done'

Loading the usr-tests.md.xz mfsroot at boot:

load -t mfs_root /usr-tests.md.xz

Getting FreeBSD ports to compile on FreeBSD 7 for pain and profit (directions worked with CURRENT @ ~r267851):

1. echo `'.include <bsd.own.mk>' > /usr/share/mk/bsd.own.mk`.
2. Export the following variables:

   # Not sure how to get things to work with gcc; ran into -Wshadow problems
   # with libarchive and times(3), and gcc on the OS didn't support all of the
   # keywords that clang did (restrict for instance).

   export CC=clang FORCE_PKG_REGISTER=1 MK_ICONV=no MK_TESTS=no MAKESYSPATH=/usr/share/mk NO_WARNING_PKG_INSTALL_EOL=1

3. Turn off spawn.h/posix_spawn support in lib/libarchive/freebsd_config.h.
4. Revert FreeBSD @ r252231 so sed will compile again.
5. Install `usr.bin/bmake lib/lzma lib/libarchive lib/libedit usr.bin/sed usr.bin/tar`
6. Remove RUN_DEPENDS for info in bsd.port.mk.
7. Install `devel/autoconf devel/automake devel/m4`
